1.0b2q2
*	Compiles more easily on more systems
*	Zone lookups work

1.0b1
*	Restarted work after long hiatus, works under 2.0.33 kernel
*	More meaningful error messages returned
*	Successfully mounts `netatalk' exported volumes
*	Support server notifications

1.0a6 (1997/09/30)
*	MkLinux port
*	Fixed handling of interrupted system calls
*	Bug fixes

1.0a5 (1997/07/26)
*	Fixed ATP-- should work a lot better
*	Fixed ASP so that writing to volumes should work
*	Fixed tickle timers, sort of-- it'll be ok for now
-	Same (low) speed as Finder copying large files to our Centris
	running System 7.5 file sharing...

1.0a4 (1997/07/19)
*	Fixed ASP sequence synchronization after transaction failure
*	Fixed timeout logic
*	Fixed NBP lookup
*	Fixed kernel-level socket code
*	Implemented client-side AEP and RTMP
*	Authenticated (cleartext) login

1.0a3 (1997/07/12)
*	Rewrote NBP lookup and afptest, work better

1.0a2 (1997/05/11)
*	Fixed the distribution so that it will now at least compile

